# Feature Pull Requests

## Merge Policy

- **All feature work merges via pull request.** Do not push feature changes directly to protected
  branches (e.g. `main`, `master`, `release/*`).
- **One PR per feature**, not one PR per commit. The branch may contain multiple commits; the PR
  description is the single delivery record for the whole feature.
- Open or update the PR after **`test-runner`** and the second **`doc-sync`** pass complete, unless
  the user explicitly requests an earlier draft PR for review.
- Small fixes with no SDD may still use a PR; use `N/A` in SDD/ADR sections and keep verification
  evidence in section 3.

## PR Title

Use the feature slug or a short feature name that matches `docs/sdd/<feature-slug>.md` when an SDD
exists.

## Required PR Description Sections

Copy the template below into the PR body. Fill every subsection; use `None` or `N/A` when a
subsection does not apply — do not omit headings.

```markdown
